the introduction of cheap flights and low budget competition regarding offering flight tickets. It has modified the face of tourism in the country, and has increased the number of people and tourists. For this reason, tourism is the most rewarding industry in the past few years. Thus, cheap flights have been introduced on almost every small and large airport. Flying with cheap flight companies is not a punishment anymore. As a fact, ordinary people (for the first time in the history of Poland) can afford to go on holiday. A great majority of urban women must spend their reasonable salary(which is around 500 euro) to make ends meet. Hence, they cannot afford luxurious European holidays, as they are not that cheap and generally speaking, they cannot easily take holidays of this kind. Most of them can only dream of exotic destinations (Australia, Thailand, Mauritius, the USA etc.) cheap flights let everybody dream come true, so they dream now!

Secondly, cheap flights have changed the way of shopping. Transferring money to the different European countries has become cheaper than ever. So if anyone of you have friends in Croatia, just call them up and ask whether they could lend you some money. For easy shopping, there are as well cheap flights offered by online shopings. We all know about such companies as Amazon, or e-bay. Online shopings have reached the big screen now. It seems that only one click can change our symmetry very fast!

As well, cheap flights make travelling cheap. Experience
